1
00:00:05,601 --> 00:00:09,161
Not reject—means to acknowledge.

2
00:00:09,505 --> 00:00:12,575
[Recalibration | Shastra, Sadhu, 
Guru, Vaishnav]

3
00:00:12,715 --> 00:00:18,255
It is just like, if you have a disease, 
so you are saying, “I should reject this.”

4
00:00:18,255 --> 00:00:22,285
No, we are saying, “First acknowledge 
that you have this disease.”

5
00:00:22,515 --> 00:00:28,475
Earlier I showed, you know, I have 
a blood pressure reading instrument.

6
00:00:28,508 --> 00:00:32,308
It gives your blood pressure 
and your heart rate.

7
00:00:32,606 --> 00:00:36,626
So, you need to first ... 
not just reject it,

8
00:00:36,626 --> 00:00:40,286
but acknowledge it’s giving 
false readings.

9
00:00:40,522 --> 00:00:43,432
That means it needs 
to be recalibrated.

10
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:47,385
Doesn't mean you don't need it;
it needs to be recalibrated.

11
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:52,682
So, you need to recalibrate 
your criteria for selection.

12
00:00:52,752 --> 00:00:55,082
This is what we are talking about 
in the beginning.

13
00:00:55,082 --> 00:00:57,757
What will be the proper calibration?

14
00:00:57,996 --> 00:01:01,896
Sādhu, Śāstra, Guru, Vaiṣṇava—
means revealed truth.

15
00:01:02,058 --> 00:01:07,518
When you're recalibrated to see things that way, 
then you can make proper assessments:

16
00:01:07,518 --> 00:01:10,478
this is desirable, that is undesirable,

17
00:01:10,512 --> 00:01:13,792
I should move in this direction 
and not go that way.

